Your project uses **MSTest v3 (3.8.0)** on **net8.0**. Here's what applies to you:

### Breaking changes in your code

**`[ExpectedException]` removed** (lines 9, 16) — This is the main issue. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>()` inside the test body:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

Same pattern for `Process_InvalidState_ThrowsInvalidOperation`.

### Other breaking changes (not in your code, but worth knowing)

| Change | Fix |
|---|---|
| `Assert.ThrowsException` renamed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Just use `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties.Contains()` | Use `.ContainsKey()` |
| `TestMethodAttribute("name")` constructor | Use `DisplayName = "name"` |
| Custom `TestMethodAttribute.Execute` | Override `ExecuteAsync` instead |
| net5.0–net7.0 dropped | Your net8.0 is fine ✅ |

### Key behavioral changes

- **`TestCase.Id`** generation changed — Azure DevOps test history may reset
- **`TreatDiscoveryWarningsAsErrors`** now defaults to `true`
- **Analyzer severities** upgraded — expect new warnings

